description.plain:
Alex A. Serrano Olivencia, known as Galante “El Emperador”, ALX “The Master” music producer/ sound engineer or @GalanteALX was born on February 17th, 1988 in Ponce, Puerto Rico. In 2001, he decided to move to Baltimore, Maryland, with the purpose of continuing studies and learn English, but has since moved back to Puerto Rico, where he works as a producer and sound engineer, in addition to his work as a songwriter.

At 14, he discovered his talent for music and began working as a solo artist. Two years later, in 2006, Galante met Killatonez, with whom he formed the duo Galante and Killatonez “Los Emperadores”.

After the duo disbanded, Galante started working with the renowned producer DJ Memo (Raymond Diaz), who’s produced the hits “Zun Dada” with Zion, “Montale” with Miguelito, “Photogenic” with Dalmatians, “Whip” with Andy Boy, “Bandolero Remix” with Olga Tanon and “Ella Anda Sola” with Don Omar.

Galante has also collaborated with leading exponents of the genre such Jowell y Randy, Zion y Lennox, Arcangel, De La Ghetto, Farruko, J Alvarez, Trebol Clan, Lui-g 21+, Gotay, among others.

He is a very prolific artist, releasing one album per year for the past five years. His discography includes the albums “El Emperador” (2010), “Tu Juguetito Sexual, vol. 1” (2012), “Tu Juguetito Sexual (Sexy Edition)” (2013), “El Inmortal” (2014), “Un Superdotado” (2015) and “Pre-Momentum: The Mixtape” (2016).

Besides music, Galante also loves technology since he was very young, and has created many websites, such as El Genero, which has since become one of the main websites about Reggaetón and latin urban music biggest webpages.

On (2018) the artist/ latin music producer has release Momentum Album one of the biggest discography trending on latin urban music & Reggaeton sensual/ romantic idol.

The first artist, music producer of own label Double Dice Music, Music engineer of Top Audio Mastering Company, Network developer and programmer of the latin music community most rated again has made history developing a platform for fans in communication with the artist called http://www.wikifans.club The reggaetón and trap news pages to help new talents promotion on Latin music genre called http://www.wikireggaeton.com Additional creator of the top news page http://www.wikiurbano.com and owner of Youtube Network called Viralx Network. Now trending on https://videos.artistaviral.tv/

Galante “El Emperador” an multi-facetic artist and executive music producer is currently the producer one of the top trending feminine artist of Puerto Rico called Indy Flow singer/ rapper and songwritter and know as “La Diosa” of Latin Urban & Reggaetón genre. (2018) Releasing first album title: Cash Flow Album.

https://genius.com/artists/Indy-flow

songs.lyrics:
1 ContributorSi El Mundo Se Acabara Lyrics[Letra de "Si El Mundo Se Acabara"]

[Intro]
(Si el mundo se acabara, -bara, -bara)
Ajá (Me llevo tu mirada; tu mirada; tu mirada)
(Y de tu cara)
Ah
Galante "El Emperador"

[Verso 1]
Me decidí a venir
Hace tiempo que no paso por acá (Por acá)
Sí, lo sé, eh, que me he alejado de usted
Pero aquí estoy rendido a tus pies
Y ya sé (Y ya sé), que no he sido el mejor (Que no he sido el mejor)
Y me ha ido 'e lo peor, ya recibí mi lección (Ah-ah)
Solo quiero dar amo-o-o-or
Ya que no me llevo con el dolo-o-or

[Coro]
Si el mundo se acabara lo perdería todo
Pero conmigo me llevo tu mirada y esas hermosas caricias
Y la silueta de tu cuerpo y de tu cara
Aún caminó descalzo (Descalzo), con la mente en blanco (Con la mente en blanco)
A mi Dios adorando, a mi bebé amando, oh-oh
La vida se hizo pa' todos llegar
Aunque a veces pensemos de más
Cuantas misiones hay que completar
Para la meta poder alcanzar
Luego que llegue no me vo'a salir
Pero al diablo no le vo'a servir
Solo existe una verdad (Oh), en mis sueños llegará
You might also like[Verso 2]
¡Yo!, solo quiero la verdad y la consigo muy fácil soñando
Con Él me voy desahogando
Él me va aconsejando por la vida guiando
Hay veces que quiero cantar
Hay veces que quiero llorar (Oh-oh-oh)
Hay veces que quiero gritar
Hay veces que quiero expresarme
Cuando sientas que ya e' un poco tarde
Y de todos ya quiera' alejarte
Nunca optes por desanimarte
Dale mente a no quitarte (No quitarte; no quitarte; Oh-oh)
Ahora no puedes quitarte (-te, eh)
Quizá que al conquistarte ya la vida apena' va a comenzar
Dicen que la vida se acaba y no se acaba na'
Yo sigo a Diosito aunque venga el Orden Mundial
Ya no se hable más na' (Na')
Nara-nara-na
No me he ido vamo' allá (No me he ido vamo' allá)
No me he ido estamo' aquí (Aquí)
Cada vez cerca de ti (De ti)
Seguimos aquí
Adorándote a ti mi Dios

[Outro]
(Si el mundo—, si el mundo se acabara)
ALX "The Master" (Me llevo tu mirada)
Galante "El Emperador"
Los Anunnakis
E' yo' Fade "El Que Pone La Presión"
El Equipo Ganador
